GarantiBank International in Talks for 100-Million Euro Loan

-- B y   S t e p h e n   M o r r i s
-- 
2011-05-27T16:19:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/garantibank-international-in-talks-for-100-million-euro-loan.html
GarantiBank International NV, a unit
of  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN) , began talks with banks to raise a
100 million-euro ($143 million) term loan to refinance debt.  The one-year facility will pay interest of 60 basis points
over the  London  interbank offered rate, and will replace a term
loan of the same size signed in Oct. 2010, according to
Bloomberg data. Lenders will get an additional 50 basis points
of fees. A basis point is 0.01 percentage point.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Morris in London at 
 smorris39@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 